  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. Since a 10-ride pass costs $12.50 and <span class=\"italic\">g</span> is the number of 10-ride passes Tony buys in a month, the expression <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"12 point 5 0 g \"></span> represents the amount Tony spends on 10-ride passes in a month. Since a single-ride pass costs $1.50 and <span class=\"italic\">t</span> is the number of single-ride passes Tony buys in a month, the expression <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"1 point 5 0 t \"></span> represents the amount Tony spends on single-ride passes in a month. Therefore, the sum <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"12 point 5 0 g, plus 1 point 5 0 t \"></span> represents the amount he spends on the two types of passes in a month. Since Tony spends a total of $80 on passes in a month, this expression can be set equal to 80, producing <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"12 point 5 0 g, plus 1 point 5 0 t, equals 80\"></span>.<p>Choices A and B are incorrect. The expression <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"g plus t \"></span> represents the total number of the two types of passes Tony buys in a month, not the amount Tony spends, which is equal to 80, nor the cost of one of each pass, which is equal to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"1 point 5 0, plus 12 point 5 0\"></span>. Choice C is incorrect and may result from reversing the cost for each type of pass Tony buys in a month.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
